f=Engineering/rank/operational/tool/rank-tool-requirements.md · p=What rank needs, what happens without each. external tool call plan-locked (Rail sandboxed (Rail 2); rank runs data changes (Rail edits production directly. · h2:Requirements=\| Need \| Tool / access \| Used by \| Without it \| · h2:Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Requirements=\| claude-seo plugin \| AgriciDaniel/claude-seo (MIT) — runtime install, proposed connector §5 \| claude-seo-integration \| Method-only SEO (siblings), labeled reduced-automation \| · h2:Requirements=\| Site read access (crawl the site, read robots/sitemap) \| HTTP read of the site \| technical-seo-execution, structured-data-geo \| Can't audit; escalate \| · h2:Requirements=\| Google SEO APIs (optional) \| GSC / PageSpeed / CrUX / Indexing / GA4 creds \| claude-seo-integration (seo-google) \| Free/estimated data only, labeled \| · h2:Requirements=\| Plugin extensions (optional) \| Firecrawl, DataForSEO, image-gen (separate installers) \| claude-seo-integration \| Core plugin only \| · h2:Requirements=\| Schema validation \| Schema.org / Google structured-data tooling \| structured-data-geo \| Manual validation, labeled \| · h2:Explicit non-needs prohibitions (by design)=**No direct production edits** rank diagnoses specs; mia/raj implement through dev review quinn's gate. plugin analyzes/generates; never auto-applies live site., **No SEO strategy business-facing measurement ownership** that's kai (boundary skill)., **No data change execution** (Rail 3)., **No shipping plugin's community-promo footer** operator output. · n=claude-seo plugin treated dated tool (its SEO facts INP, schema deprecations dates); verify high-stakes facts against current Google guidance (ops's volatility-split discipline)., Plugin Google API creds proposed connectors surfaced operator deployment (plan §5). · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=rank department's heaviest consumer web-scraping analysis tools. SEO domain demands competitive intelligence, SERP monitoring, content extraction cannot done without accessing live web content. · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| Tool \| Source \| Purpose \| Always-on \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\|------\|--------\|---------\|-----------\| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Firecrawl MCP** \| [github.com/mcp/firecrawl](https://github.com/mcp/firecrawl/firecrawl-mcp-server) \| Primary SEO reconnaissance: scrape competitor pages, search for SERP features, map competitor site structure (sitemap + URL discovery), structured data extraction (Schema.org validation), deep_research for competitive landscape analysis. 10+ tools. Free tier available. \| ⚠️ On-demand — core tool for technical-seo-execution and structured-data-geo \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Crawl4AI** \| [github.com/unclecode/crawl4ai](https://github.com/unclecode/crawl4ai) — Apache 2.0 \| Content inventory: deep-crawl competitor sites → clean Markdown → content analysis. BFS/DFS strategies for site structure mapping. No API keys needed. \| ❌ No — Python tool; use for content audits and site structure analysis \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Scrapling** \| [github.com/D4Vinci/Scrapling](https://github.com/D4Vinci/Scrapling) — BSD 3-Clause \| Competitor sites with anti-bot protection: bypass Cloudflare Turnstile when competitor sites block standard crawlers. Adaptive element relocator handles site structure changes between crawls. Spider API for continuous monitoring. \| ❌ No — escalate only when Firecrawl or Crawl4AI are blocked \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Website Cloner** \| [github.com/horuz-ai/claude-plugins](https://github.com/horuz-ai/claude-plugins) (website-cloner SKILL) \| SERP layout analysis: clone competitor landing pages to test SEO structure, meta tag extraction, heading hierarchy analysis. Pixel-perfect clone for competitive page structure comparison. \| ❌ No — expensive pipeline; use /clone-website for targeted competitor analysis \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=**Tool selection logic (rank-specific):** Standard competitor page scraping Firecrawl scrape Full site structure mapping Crawl4AI deep-crawl Firecrawl map Competitor blocks crawlers Scrapling (stealth mode) Visual SERP/landing page analysis Website Cloner See Engineering/MCP-MARKETPLACE.md full setup instructions department-wide tool catalog.